text: __NOTOC__ Lautaro was a 16th-century indigenous leader in what is now Chile. It may also refer to: ==Persons== *Lautaro Acosta, Argentine footballer *Lautaro Baeza, Argentine–Chilean footballer *Lautaro Chávez, Argentine footballer *Lautaro Delgado, Argentine film and TV actor *Lautaro Martínez, Argentine footballer *Lautaro Murúa, Chilean–Argentine film and TV actor *Lautaro Núñez Atencio, Chilean historian *Lautaro Parisi, Argentine footballer *Lautaro Schinnea, Argentine footballer ==Institutions== *Lautaro Lodge, a lodge created by Francisco de Miranda to promote the emancipation of the South American colonies ==Places== *Lautaro, Chile, a town and municipality in southern Chile's Araucanía Region *Lautaro (volcano), a volcano in the Southern Patagonian Ice Fields, Chile *Lautaro Island, a island in the west of Lemaire Island in Gerlache Strait, Antarctic Peninsula ==Ships== * There are eight ships of the Chilean Navy named Lautaro: see Chilean ship Lautaro Category:Masculine given names Category:South American given names
title: Lautaro (disambiguation)
